 I knew that Karabo was abused, the mourner and a friend of the Karabo Mokoena, Neo Mohlabane, said at the memorial service in honour of the life of young woman allegedly killed by her boyfriend. The emotional service was held this afternoon.Mohlabane said this while speaking at Karabo&#8217;s memorial service which was held at the Diepkloof Hall in Soweto.&#8220;Karabo was very strong and bold but she had a vulnerable side that she didn&#8217;t show to everyone. Her favourite line when she was facing challenges was, &#8220;it is well&#8221;.&#8220;Little did I know that our last weekend together would be a farewell to her and her last words to me were: I love you, said Mohlabane.Family and friends paid their final respect to Karabo Mokoena who was allegedly killed by her ex-boyfriend.Mokoena s burnt body was found in a veld in Lyndhurst, Johannesburg, on April 29. She was reported missing the day before. Neo also stated that Karabo had complained about her boyfriend, Sandile, claiming that he was physically aggressive towards her.The boyfriend, Sandile Kagiso Mantsoe, 27, is expected back to make a formal bail application in the Johannesburg Magistrate s Court on May 24. He faces two charges for premeditated murder and a count for defeating the ends of justice.Mantsoe was in a relationship with Mokoena for seven months and worked as a forex trader. He was reportedly wanted for the alleged robbery of R2.5-million in Forex.-Simangele Legodi 